name: Brent Lineberry
note: Web and app developer. Coffee, beer, and running, in any order.

content.html:
Inspired by my recent Podcasts post, here are my current YouTube subscriptions:

Reducing Car Dependency

  • Not Just Bikes: A Canadian living in Amsterdam teaching how cars ruin cities.
  • Strong Towns: Strong Towns tends to take an economic approach in arguing for reducing car dependency in cities. Cars: they’re not just bad for the environment, our health, and traffic, they’re also bad for our cities’ finances.

Running/Cycling

  • Atlanta Track Club: Mostly short promotional videos, but I’m an ATC member, so figured I’d subscribe.
  • BikeBlogger: This guy videos his bike commute to work. A nice peaceful discussion of a topic with the background of a flywheel and commute commentary. “UP the hill, UP the hill”.
  • Global Cycling Network: They put out a ton of content, most of it very good and interesting.
  • Park Tool: Bicycle maintenance instructions, tips, and products.
  • Phil Gaimon: Fun cycling videos from an ex-pro.
  • The Mocko Show: Entertaining videos following the training of runner Chris Mocko. I haven’t seen a new video in a disappointingly long time though.

Food/Cooking

  • Alex: Formerly titled “French Guy Cooking”, Alex takes obsessive deep dives into different cooking topics with a heavy dose of engineering.
  • Pailin’s Kitchen: The best Thai cooking channel/website I’ve found. Videos for every recipe on Hot Thai Kitchen. It is a game changer when learning a new cuisine.
  • Peaceful Cuisine: Calming videos of the host cooking. No words, just the sounds of food prep and soothing background music.

Woodworking/DIY

  • April Wilkerson: Building things. All kinds of things.
  • Ex Materia Woodworking: A friend of mine and a fine woodworker.
  • Highland Woodworking: A local woodworking shop with a global reach.
  • RenaissanceWW: Woodworking with hand tools.
  • treebangham: The most wholesome woodworking videos you’ll ever see.

Miscellaneous/Interesting

  • Joseph’s Machines: A modern Rube Goldberg, Joseph makes ridiculously creative and complicated contraptions.
  • Mark Rober: An engineer using science for interesting projects.
  • USA Curling: I like curling and wish I saw it more often than just the Winter Olympics.

name: Unit Testing Salesforce Bounced Email Addresses in Apex

content.html:
Recently my team at work ran into a bug in an Apex class around trying to send email to a bounced email address. When going to write a unit test to confirm the behavior, we ran into a problem: the Contact object has a boolean IsEmailBounced field, but it has no setter. How can we simulate a bounced email in a unit test when we can't set the field?

We found the answer on the Trailblazer Community site.

Turns out IsEmailBounced is a computed field based on EmailBouncedDate and EmailBouncedReason. Setting those fields in the unit test allowed us to test and fix the bug.

Here's the documentation on the Contact object, including the IsEmailBounced, EmailBouncedDate, and EmailBouncedReason fields.

content.html:
A friend recently asked me what podcasts I listen to, so I thought I'd update my previous list.

“Top Tier” Podcasts

I will listen to new episodes of these before I'll listen to anything else.

  • 99% Invisible: Each episode is an exploration of an interesting, probably esoteric topic.
  • Homebrewed Christianity: Interviews with a variety of theologians.
  • The War on Cars: Great discussions on why cars are bad for society.
  • Wait Wait… Don't Tell Me!: The original NPR news quiz! Hilarious game show focusing on the previous week's news.

“I Like These Too” Podcasts

I'll listen to these if I've already caught up on my top-tier podcasts.

  • Micromobility: Exploration of the "light individual transport" space from a business disruption perspective.
  • Milk Street Radio: A food, recipes, and cooking show.
  • The Splendid Table: Another food, recipes, and cooking show.
  • This American Life: This used to be a top-tier show, but now I have to decide if I'm in an emotional state to handle potentially heartbreaking stories. Each episode has a theme and then 3 or 4 stories around that theme.

“I'm Subscribed, but I Don't Really Listen” Podcasts

  • Dirty South Soccer: An SB Nation Atlanta United podcast.
  • The Falcoholic: An SB Nation Falcons podcast.
  • Southern Fried Soccer: An AJC Atlanta United podcast.
